pageContext.claim: “And to think that the stock market is at this tremendously high number. Not that much -- you know, it was looking a little bleak for a while, but it -- it hit a certain point and then started going up. I think that's a great tribute to the fact that there's a demand.”
pageContext.analysis: The Dow Jones Industrial Average has crept back up since dipping below 20,000 in late March, but it is still several thousand points below where it was in February.
